<subSubSection id="3A18F1879A07282E8D479D743522D83B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0F983EAB896625A17846E0DF4B142C69" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C10B6AB91CB0AC55B3912FA46EAE6286" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
Palaearctic. 
<taxonomicName id="D9DA7D9527819A578BA2E5225160F085" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Boletina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Boletina polaris" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polaris">Boletina polaris</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 14) was described from arctic Siberia (
<bibRefCitation id="6F56440690CCD255756FAFEA102DE6CF" author="Lundstroem, C." journalOrPublisher="Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences. VIIIe serie. Classe Physico-Mathematique" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="1 - 33" title="DipteraNematocera aus den arctischen Gegenden Sibiriens. [Resultats scientifiques de l'Expedition Polaire Russe en 1900 - 1903, sons la direction du Baron E. Toll. Section E: Zoologie. Volume II, livr. 8.]" volume="29" year="1915">
<normalizedToken id="CA34F523C3C4C45D875DB5A35CEFF386" originalValue="Lundström">Lundstroem</normalizedToken>
1915
</bibRefCitation>
) and has been later found from the Kola Peninsula, northernmost parts of Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="2A0F9AE8DD1E49458E490C94A4340E17" author="Zaitzev, A. I." journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Fungus gnats of the fauna of Russia and adjacent regions. Part 1" year="1994">Zaitzev 1994</bibRefCitation>
), north Sweden (Lule Lappmark, 
<bibRefCitation id="5124BD6C6CA3506716AD324A9011AE42" author="Kjaerandsen, J." journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="1 - 165" title="Annotated checklist of fungus gnats from Sweden (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Diadocidiidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae)" volume="65" year="2007">Kjaerandsen et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), Norway (
<bibRefCitation id="CABE374FF6F51EF9186E6F9425F585C0" author="Soli, G." journalOrPublisher="Norwegian Journal of Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="158 - 181" title="Fungus gnats (Diptera, Mycetophilidae) from Finnmark, northern Norway" volume="59" year="2012">
<normalizedToken id="9E11AA070A1A1E9A5DC04E6B5E3B9FAC" originalValue="Søli">Soli</normalizedToken>
and Rindal 2012
</bibRefCitation>
), Germany (
<bibRefCitation id="A02F3263FDFCD9D6EFFD99D3CE07DCC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Chandler 2004</bibRefCitation>
) and the Italian Alps (
<bibRefCitation id="923379F77AE11E68C0EBF30B0E417E1D" author="Kurina, O." editor="Ziegler, J." journalOrPublisher="Ampyx-Verlag, Halle (Saale)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Diptera Stelviana - A dipterological perspective on a changing alpine landscape. Studia Dipterologica Supplement." year="2008">Kurina 2008</bibRefCitation>
). New for Finland. Finnish records are from SW Lapland (mid boreal zone) and eastern Lapland (north boreal zone).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6CF3743FF4176ECE50C0501D89E603FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="B8ED76A26980343B85288479058ACD2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A5A61A0BC3944C7C0270583EBCAC301B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Finnish collecting localities are characterized by small lotic waters surrounded by pristine or seminatural boreal forests. Immature stages are unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
